   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The first step is to apply the specified voltages to the terminals
for the units.</p>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that <xref href="Bruce_Preparations_with_Power_Off_CPT_0000916378.dita"
                        scope="local"
                        type="concept"
                        class="- topic/xref "/> have been performed.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i> and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection
Diagram</i> for the specifications of the rectifier mains voltage,
frequency and phase sequence.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i> and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection
Diagram</i> for the specifications of the DC input power voltage and
polarity.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Connect the rectifier mains voltage to the
open rectifier mains input breaker(s). Keep the breaker(s) open!</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Measure and check with a properly rated
measuring device that the rectifier mains voltage, frequency and phase
sequence are according to specifications.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Connect the DC input power voltage to the open
inverter input switches. Keep the switches open!</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Measure and check with a properly rated measuring
device that the DC input power voltage (L+, L- and ground) and polarity
are according to specifications.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS 3pMBS noMBS"
                platform="PxW WxW"
                class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">On the bypass:</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i> and <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection Diagram</i> for
the specifications of the bypass mains voltage, frequency and phase
sequence.</p>
                     <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">The same bypass mains source must
be used for all units.</note>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Connect the bypass mains voltage to the open bypass mains input
breaker. Keep the breaker open!</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Measure and check with a properly rated measuring device that
the bypass mains voltage, frequency and phase sequence are according
to specifications.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
